        <num>CC 676</num>
        <heading>676.  Adjoining wall</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 676.  Adjoining wall.
When a solid masonry wall adjoins another estate, the neighbor has a right to make it a common wall, in whole or in part, by paying to its owner one-half of the current value of the wall, or of the part that he wishes to make common, and one-half of the value of the soil on which the wall is built.</p>
        </content>
